*\\n\\nI'm figuring out how to run Route.toFunction, which needs an ActorSystem provider. I need to manage the pekko-actor and stream dependencies while keeping an eye on shutting down the ActorSystem properly. Maybe I can add tests with before and after methods, but it seems I can't run compile-time checks. \\n\\nCreating a class like `Pekko_http_2_13Test` might be useful, and I should ensure all public classes are top-level. Testing the public APIs sounds better than focusing on the core model alone.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Setting up Actor System in Route**\\n\\nI'm planning to write a helper function withSystem that creates an actor system and handles termination properly with Await.result. I’ll also use the system's execution context for dispatching.\\n\\nFor the route, I need to define paths and methods for retrieving items and posting data. I'm aware that the entity requires an unmarshaller for string materialization, and the routing will return a Future[HttpResponse]. \\n\\nIt looks like response handling should ensure I deal with strict entities, and I need to account for potential rejections if the method isn't found.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Cni0XfUo5HWzoFq5TyYiBl8c|fc_02ebe172aaccf27a0169fac8bc4f30819780472de36c881a69", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/tmp/pekko_inspect/org/apache/pekko/http/scaladsl/client/RequestBuilding.scala", "limit": 140}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"/tmp/pekko_inspect/org/apache/pekko/http/scaladsl/client/RequestBuilding.scala\",\"limit\":140}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1962, "output": 880, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37146, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778043055117, "responseId": "resp_02ebe172aaccf27a0169fac8af9bf481978cc1c308fab9ec01"}}
